File Handler
The file handler is responsible for reading and writing the score of the game to a file.

Functions
The file handler contains two function for reading from a file and writing to a file.

    • save_score(json_dict):
      This method saves the score of the game in a json file in form of a dictionary. Either it saves the data to the existing file „score_yatzee.json“ or it creates a new one if one doesn’t already exist.
    • get_score:
      This mehtod reads the score of the game from the json file „score_yatzee.json“. If the file is empty, it will return None. If the file is not empty, it will return the file content.

